\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\fs32 1. What is system bus\par
ANS:- A system bus is a communication system in a computer that comprises three main buses: the data bus, which carries data between the CPU and memory; the address bus, responsible for transmitting memory addresses; and the control bus, managing signals for coordinating and controlling various system operations. Together, these buses facilitate efficient communication and data transfer among different components within a computer system.\par

