\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\fs32 1. List out the types of system bus.\par
ANS:- The types of system buses are:\par
1. Data Bus: Transmits data between the CPU, memory, and peripheral devices.\par
2. Address Bus: Sends memory addresses from the CPU to specify data locations.\par
3. Control Bus: Manages control signals for coordinating system operations.\par
2. Describe the working of system bus.\par
ANS:- The system bus operates as follows:\par
\par
1. Data Transfer:\par
   - The system bus includes a bidirectional data bus that enables the transfer of binary data between the central processing unit (CPU), memory, and peripheral devices. Data is transmitted in the form of electrical signals over this pathway.\par
\par
2. Addressing and Control:\par
   - The address bus, a unidirectional pathway, allows the CPU to specify memory locations by sending memory addresses. Simultaneously, the control bus manages control signals coordinating activities such as read and write operations, interrupts, and overall system control.\par
\par
In essence, the system bus facilitates seamless communication and coordination among different components of a computer system, ensuring efficient data transfer and system operation.\par
3. Do a practical to identify the system bus.\par
ANS:- 1. Physical Inspection:\par
   - Open the computer case and identify the motherboard.\par
   - Look for labels or markings on the motherboard to determine the bus type.\par
\par
2. Software-Based Method:\par
